@
text
@d1 7
a7 7
Skippy is best described as a full-screen task-switcher for X11.
It tries to provide an alternative when taskbars or regular
task-switchers aren't the most efficient way of switching tasks
(like when you have a lot of applications open). When activated
(currently only through a hotkey), it will arrange and scale snapshots
of all windows on the current desktop and it'll let you pick a
window using a mouse or a keyboard.
@


